                  <join result="offencePlace" targOrder="Y" targets="t18310908-71-off405 t18310908-71-crimeloc408"></join>. On the 23rd of August, about seven o'clock in the evening, I saw the prisoner in Charles-street, about fifty yards from my masters', in company with two other boys - he had this jacket wrapped up as it is now; I took it from him, and took it back to the shop; it is my masters', and had hung inside the door.</p>
               <p>Prisoner's Defence (written). I was going on an errand; two boys ran up to me, and said,</p>
               <p>"Hold this a moment," at the same time forcing a bundle into my hands; and before I had time to reflect on the circumstance, I was taken into custody.</p>
